PROPOSAL: canopy-initial-2026-03-03
STATUS: pending
TIER: T1
FILES: core/leaf.py, core/prism.py, core/crown.py
AUTHOR: Shiva (Claude Code) + Sean Campbell

SUMMARY
-------
Initial implementation of the full Canopy layer — LEAF, PRISM, CROWN.
Three files, one ratification. They form a pipeline:
  LEAF fetches → PRISM verifies → CROWN composes and witnesses.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LEAF — Library, External, Archive, Fetch
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Verified source retrieval. No SEO slop. Trusted sources only.

Supported: Wikipedia REST API (primary). Others (LoC, NASA, NIH) as
extension points — stubs with the same interface.

Design:
  - fetch(source, query) → SourceResult dict
  - search(query, sources=None) → list[SourceResult]
  - cache: SQLite-backed (leaf.db, caller provides). TTL 24h.
  - confidence: Wikipedia=0.85 base. Adjusted by article quality signals
    (length, references, disambiguation). Oral sources = 0.3 max.
  - SourceResult: {source, url, title, content, confidence, fetched_at, cached}

Public API:
  init_tables(db_path) → None
  fetch(db_path, source, query) → Optional[dict]
  search(db_path, query, sources=None, max_results=5) → list[dict]
  clear_cache(db_path, older_than_hours=24) → int

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PRISM — Prove, Reference, Inspect, Source, Match
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Source verification. Takes a claim and a source, determines if they match.

Entity classification:
  verifiable    — public record (public figure, institution, dated event)
  oral-consented — private individual who has explicitly consented
  unverifiable   — insufficient evidence to classify

Verification pipeline:
  1. classify_entity(name, context) → {class, confidence, reasoning}
  2. verify(claim, source_result) → VerificationResult
     - Exact: string match in source content
     - Semantic: LLM fleet comparison (best-effort, fleet=free)
     - Score: 0.0–1.0. Threshold 0.7 = verified.
  3. write_verification(loam_db_path, knowledge_id, result) — stores
     confidence and verification notes back to LOAM atom.

Public API:
  classify_entity(name, context="") → dict
  verify(claim, source_result, llm_router=None) → dict
  write_verification(loam_db_path, username, knowledge_id, result) → None
  batch_verify(claims, source_results, llm_router=None) → list[dict]

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CROWN — Compose, Release, Output, Witness, Nurture
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Output layer. The launch benchmark. Implements Witness properly.

Benchmark status (from README):
  Compose ✅ Release ✅ Output ✅ Witness ⚠️ Nurture ❌

This implementation completes Witness. Nurture is stubbed (UTETY hooks
are not yet wired — Nurture requires UTETY Campus integration, out of scope).

Compose: format_response(content, format="markdown"|"plain"|"json") → str
Release: release(content, target="user"|"safe"|"pigeon") → dict
Output:  artifact(content, title, source_type, username, loam_db_path) → int
         → ingests the output into LOAM as a knowledge atom (closes the loop)
Witness: record(title, content, agent, username, witness_db_path) → str
         → formal tamper-evident record of what was produced
         → SHA256 hash of content stored alongside timestamp + agent
Nurture: stub — logs intent, returns {"status": "not_implemented"}

Public API:
  format_response(content, fmt="markdown") → str
  release(content, target="user", metadata=None) → dict
  artifact(content, title, source_type, username, loam_db_path,
           vine_db_path=None) → int
  record(title, content, agent, username, witness_db_path) → str
  init_witness(db_path) → None
  nurture(username, community=None) → dict  # stub

